{"word":"ὠκύς","slug":"ὠκύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὠκύς</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <el>ὀξύς</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>quick, swift, fleet</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <el>πόδας ὠκύς</el>, of Achilles, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>πόδας ὠκέα</el>, of Iris, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>= <el>ὀξύς</el>, <i>sharp</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-έως</el>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; but in form <el>ὦκα</el>, formed like <el>τάχα</el>, often in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>degrees of Comparison, <a href='S:regular, regularly'>regul.</a> <el>ὠκύτερος, ὠκύτατος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <a href='S:irregular'>irreg.</a> <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a>, <el>ὤκιστος</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}